===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|髟|犮|c1=s|c2=p|t1=long hair|ls=psc}}.

The original form {{zh-l|*𩠙}} was composed of {{zh-l|*首}} and {{zh-l|*犬}}. According to Takashi Takada ({{lang|ja|高田忠周}}), {{lang|zh|犬}} is an abbreviation of {{och-l|犮}}.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-pu}}. Alternatively, it may be derived from {{och-l|發|to sprout}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

